<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="pest_tag">PEST Tag</a> - A <a href="#cTerminalRegion">C-terminal</a> tag that can be added to <a href="#protein">proteins</a> to increase their <a href="#endogenous">endogenous</a> <a href="#degredation">degradation</a> rate. Termed "PEST" because the peptide is rich in proline (P), glutamate (E), serine (S), and threonine (T).